<fr:p>A <fr:em>Grothendieck pretopology</fr:em>, or a <fr:em>basis for a <fr:link
type="local"
href="rs-0079.xml"
addr="rs-0079"
title="Grothendieck topology">Grothendieck
topology</fr:link></fr:em>,
consists of, for each object <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  C]]></fr:tex>, a collection <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K(x)]]></fr:tex> of families of
morphisms with codomain <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>, so that:
<fr:ul><fr:li><fr:em>isomorphisms</fr:em>: for every <fr:link
type="local"
href="rs-0002.xml"
addr="rs-0002"
title="Isomorphism">isomorphism</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\xrightarrow {f} y]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\{f\}\in  K(y)]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:em>stability</fr:em>: for every family <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\{x_i\xrightarrow {f_i}x\in  K(x)\}]]></fr:tex> and any map
  <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y\xrightarrow {g} x]]></fr:tex>, there exists a family <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\{y_j\xrightarrow {h_j} y\}\in  K(y)]]></fr:tex> such that
  for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[j]]></fr:tex>, there exists an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i]]></fr:tex> and a map <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[y_j\xrightarrow {k} x_i]]></fr:tex> such that
  <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[gh_j = f_ik]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:em>transitivity</fr:em>: for every family <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\{x_i\xrightarrow {f_i}x\in  K(x)\}]]></fr:tex> and for every family of
  families <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\{x_{ij}\xrightarrow {g_{ij}} x_i\}\in  K(x_i)]]></fr:tex>, the family of composites
  <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_ig_{ij}]]></fr:tex> is in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K(x)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ul></fr:p><fr:p>The <fr:em>topology generated by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex></fr:em> is the Grothendieck topology wherein a
<fr:link
type="local"
href="rs-0061.xml"
addr="rs-0061"
title="Sieve">sieve</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> covers an object <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T\subseteq  S]]></fr:tex> for
some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[T\in  K(x)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
